<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC, EURATOM, ECSC) No 2689/95 of 17 November 1995 introducing special measures to terminate the service of temporary staff of the European Communities as a result of the accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus (E&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 2689/95, millega kehtestatakse erimeetmed Euroopa &uuml;henduste ajutiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate teenistuse l&otilde;petamiseks seoses Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisega 17. november 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing a Single Council and a Single Commission of the European Communities, and in particular Article 24 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;htse n&otilde;ukogu ja &uuml;htse komisjoni asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 24, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal made by the Commission after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse ettepanekut, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Court of Justice (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Kohtu arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Court of Auditors (4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse kontrollikoja arvamust (4) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by Regulation (EC, Euratom, ECSC) No 2688/95 (5), the Council adopted special measures to terminate the service of officials of the European Communities as a result of the accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 2688/95 (5) kehtestas n&otilde;ukogu erimeetmed Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike teenistuse l&otilde;petamiseks seoses Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisega; (6) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, as a result of the said accession, it is also advisable to adopt similar measures in respect of certain temporary staff on contracts of indefinite duration, by means of a Regulation couched as far as possible in similar terms; </inglise>
<eesti> seoses nimetatud &uuml;hinemisega on soovitatav v&otilde;tta v&otilde;imalikult sarnaseid tingimusi sisaldava m&auml;&auml;rusega sarnased meetmed ka teatavate ajutiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud m&auml;&auml;ramata t&auml;htajaga t&ouml;&ouml;leping; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the purpose of these measures is to enable preference to be given to Austrian, Finnish and Swedish nationals when the posts thus released are filled; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuste meetmete eesm&auml;rk on seada Austria, Soome ja Rootsi kodanikud sel viisil vabastatud ametikohtade t&auml;itmisel eelisolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is clear that temporary staff carrying out their duties, as specified in Article 2 (c) of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities, in the political groups in the European Parliament would not be eligible for termination of service in order to enable Austrian, Finnish and Swedish nationals to be recruited in sufficient numbers and with normal career prospects if the age limit were set at 55 as was the case for officials; </inglise>
<eesti> on selge, et ajutiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate puhul, kes t&auml;idavad &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste artikli 2 punktis c s&auml;testatud kohustusi Euroopa Parlamendi poliitilistes fraktsioonides, ei saa kasutada teenistuse l&otilde;petamist selleks, et oleks v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta piisav arv normaalsete t&ouml;&ouml;alaste v&auml;ljavaadetega Austria, Soome ja Rootsi kodanikke, kui vanusepiirang on 55 aastat nagu ametnike puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the interest of the institution and to take account of the particular situation of the European Parliament, a sufficient number of Austrian, Finnish and Swedish nationals should be recruited to fill, with normal career prospects, the posts referred to in Article 2 (c); whereas the minimum age for termination of service of staff in that category should therefore be lowered to 50, </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse institutsiooni huvides ja Euroopa Parlamendi konkreetset olukorda silmas pidades tuleks t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta piisav arv Austria, Soome ja Rootsi kodanikke, et t&auml;ita artikli 2 punktis c nimetatud ametikohad ja pakkuda sealjuures normaalseid t&ouml;&ouml;alaseid v&auml;ljavaateid; seep&auml;rast tuleks k&otilde;nealuses kategoorias alandada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate minimaalset vanust teenistuse l&otilde;petamisel 50 eluaastani, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In the interests of the service, and in order to take account of requirements resulting from the accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden to the European Union, the European Parliament is authorized, until 30 June 2000, to adopt measures terminating the service of temporary staff within the meaning of Article 2 (c) of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities as specified by this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Teenistuse huvides ja v&otilde;tmaks arvesse vajadusi, mis tulenevad Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisest Euroopa Liiduga, on Euroopa Parlamendil lubatud kuni 30. juunini 2000 v&otilde;tta k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;psustatud meetmeid, et l&otilde;petada Euroopa &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste artikli 2 punktis c s&auml;testatud ajutiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate teenistus. </eesti>
<inglise> The temporary staff in question, those on contracts for an indefinite period, must have a total of at least 15 years' service and be aged at least 50. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealused ajutised t&ouml;&ouml;tajad, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud m&auml;&auml;ramata t&auml;htajaga t&ouml;&ouml;leping, peavad olema olnud teenistuses kokku v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat ning nad peavad olema v&auml;hemalt 50 aastat vanad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The number of temporary staff in respect of whom the measures referred to in Article 1 may be taken shall be thirty. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 nimetatud meetmeid v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta kolmek&uuml;mne ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> This number shall be spread over the following periods: </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud arv jaotatakse j&auml;rgmistele ajavahemikele: </eesti>
<inglise> - 2 for the period from 1 July 1995 to 30 June 1996, </inglise>
<eesti> - 2 ajavahemikul 1. juulist 1995 kuni 30. juunini 1996, </eesti>
<inglise> - 7 for the period from 1 July 1996 to 30 June 1997, </inglise>
<eesti> - 7 ajavahemikul 1. juulist 1996 kuni 30. juunini 1997, </eesti>
<inglise> - 6 for the period from 1 July 1997 to 30 June 1998, </inglise>
<eesti> - 6 ajavahemikul 1. juulist 1997 kuni 30. juunini 1998, </eesti>
<inglise> - 9 for the period from 1 July 1998 to 30 June 1999, </inglise>
<eesti> - 9 ajavahemikul 1. juulist 1998 kuni 30. juunini 1999, </eesti>
<inglise> - 6 for the period from 1 July 1999 to 30 June 2000. </inglise>
<eesti> - 6 ajavahemikul 1. juulist 1999 kuni 30. juunini 2000. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> In the interests of the service in connection with enlargement, the European Parliament shall within the limits laid down in Article 2 and after consulting the Joint Committee, select temporary staff to whom the measures terminating their service under Article 1 shall be applied, after giving staff the opportunity to express their interest. </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Parlament valib teenistuse huvides seoses laienemisega artiklis 2 s&auml;testatud piire arvestades ja p&auml;rast konsulteerimist &uuml;hiskomiteega ajutised t&ouml;&ouml;tajad, kelle suhtes kohaldatakse meetmeid, millega l&otilde;petatakse k&otilde;nealuste isikute teenistus artikli 1 alusel p&auml;rast seda, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele on antud v&otilde;imalus v&auml;ljendada oma huve. </eesti>
<inglise> For this purpose it shall take into consideration their age, ability, efficiency, conduct in the service, family situation and seniority. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks v&otilde;tab ta arvesse k&otilde;nealuste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vanust, p&auml;devust, tulemuslikkust, t&ouml;&ouml;alast k&auml;itumist, pereolusid ja teenistuse kestust. </eesti>
<inglise> Under no circumstances may these measures be applied without the consent of the member of the temporary staff concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud meetmeid ei tohi mingil juhul kohaldada ilma asjaomase ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;usolekuta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A former member of the temporary staff affected by the measure provided for in Article 1 shall be entitled to a monthly allowance equal to 70 % of the basic salary for the grade and step held at the time of departure, determined by reference to the table set out in Article 66 of the Staff Regulations in force on the first day of the month for which the allowance is payable. </inglise>
<eesti> Endisel ajutisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kelle suhtes kohaldatakse artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud meetmeid, on &otilde;igus saada igakuist toetust 70% p&otilde;hipalgast, mis tulenes tema palgaastmest ja -j&auml;rgust lahkumise hetkel ja mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse personalieeskirjade artiklis 66 esitatud tabeli p&otilde;hjal sellisena, nagu see tabel kehtib selle kuu esimesel p&auml;eval, mille eest toetust makstakse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Entitlement to the allowance shall cease not later than the last day of the month in which the former member of the temporary staff attains the age of 65 and in any event as soon as he becomes eligible, before that age, for the maximum retirement pension. </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;igus saada toetust l&otilde;peb hiljemalt selle kuu viimasel p&auml;eval, mil endine ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;taja saab 65aastaseks ja igal juhul niipea, kui ta omandab enne k&otilde;nealusesse ikka j&otilde;udmist &otilde;iguse saada maksimaalset vanaduspensioni. </eesti>
<inglise> At that point, the former member of the temporary staff shall automatically receive a retirement pension calculated in accordance with Articles 39 and 40 of the Conditions of Employment, which shall take effect on the first day of the calendar month following the month in which the allowance was paid for the last time. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul on endisel ajutisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal automaatselt &otilde;igus saada teenistustingimuste artiklite 39 ja 40 kohaselt arvutatud vanaduspensioni, mida hakatakse maksma selle kalendrikuu esimesest p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgneb viimasele toetuse maksmise kuule. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The allowance provided for in paragraph 1 shall be weighted at the rate fixed in accordance with the second subparagraph of Article 82 (1) of the Staff Regulations for the country situated inside the Community where the recipient proves he has his residence. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud toetuse suhtes kohaldatakse paranduskoefitsienti, mis kehtestatakse personalieeskirjade artikli 82 l&otilde;ike 1 teise l&otilde;igu kohaselt sellele &uuml;henduses asuvale riigile, kus saaja t&otilde;endab oma elukoha olevat. </eesti>
<inglise> If the recipient of the allowance establishes his residence in a country outside the Community, the weighting of 100 shall be applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui toetusesaaja elab v&auml;ljaspool &uuml;hendust asuvas riigis, kohaldatakse paranduskoefitsienti 100. </eesti>
<inglise> The allowance shall be expressed in Belgian francs. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetus esitatakse Belgia frankides. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be paid in the currency of the country of residence of the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda makstakse saaja elukohariigi v&auml;&auml;ringus. </eesti>
<inglise> However, if it is subject to the weighting of 100 under the second subparagraph, it shall be paid in Belgian francs. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui teise l&otilde;igu alusel kohaldatakse paranduskoefitsienti 100, makstakse toetust Belgia frankides. </eesti>
<inglise> Allowances paid in a currency other than the Belgian franc shall be calculated on the basis of the exchange rates specified in the second subparagraph of Article 63 of the Staff Regulations. </inglise>
<eesti> Muus v&auml;&auml;ringus kui Belgia frank makstavad toetused arvutatakse personalieeskirjade artikli 63 teises l&otilde;igus piiritletud vahetuskursside alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Where gross income accruing to the former member of the temporary staff from any new employment, when combined with the allowance provided for in paragraph 1, exceeds the total gross remuneration last received by him, determined by reference to the salary scales in force on the first day of the month for which the allowance is payable. the amount of the excess shall be deducted from that allowance. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui endise ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja uuel t&ouml;&ouml;kohal makstav t&ouml;&ouml;tasu koos l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud toetusega &uuml;letab kogut&ouml;&ouml;tasu, mida ametnik viimati sai ja mis on arvutatud toetuse maksmise kuu esimesel p&auml;eval kehtiva palgaastmiku p&otilde;hjal, arvatakse &uuml;leolev summa k&otilde;nealusest toetusest maha. </eesti>
<inglise> That remuneration shall be weighted as provided for in paragraph 3. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu suhtes kohaldatakse l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud paranduskoefitsienti. </eesti>
<inglise> Gross income and total gross remuneration last received, as referred to in the first subparagraph, shall mean sums paid after deduction of social security contributions but before deduction of tax. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus peetakse kogutulu ja viimati saadud kogut&ouml;&ouml;tasu all silmas summasid, millest on maha arvatud sotsiaalkindlustusmaksed, kuid mitte maksud. </eesti>
<inglise> The former member of the temporary staff shall provide any written proof which may be required and shall notify the institution of any factor which may affect his right to the allowance. </inglise>
<eesti> Endine ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;taja esitab n&otilde;utavad kirjalikud t&otilde;endid ja teavitab institutsiooni k&otilde;ikidest asjaoludest, mis v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada tema &otilde;igust saada toetust. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> As set out in Article 67 of the Staff Regulations and Articles 1, 2 and 3 of Annex VII to the Staff Regulations, family allowances shall be payable either to the recipient of the allowance provided for in paragraph 1 or to the person or persons to whom custody of the child or children has been entrusted by law or by an order of court or of the competent administrative authority; the household allowance shall be calculated by reference to that allowance. </inglise>
<eesti> Nagu on s&auml;testatud personalieeskirjade artiklis 67 ja VII lisa artiklites 1-3, makstakse peretoetused otse l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud toetuse saajale v&otilde;i isikule v&otilde;i isikutele, kellele on lapse v&otilde;i laste hooldus&otilde;igus antud seadusega v&otilde;i kohtu v&otilde;i p&auml;deva haldusasutuse korraldusega; majapidamistoetus arvutatakse k&otilde;nealuse toetuse p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Recipients of the allowance shall be entitled, in respect of themselves and persons covered by their insurance, to benefits under the sickness insurance scheme provided for in Article 72 of the Staff Regulations, provided they pay the relevant contribution, calculated on the basis of the allowance provided for in paragraph 1, and are not covered by another sickness insurance scheme by virtue of legal or statutory provisions. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetusesaajatel on &otilde;igus saada endale ja oma kindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikutele personalieeskirjade artiklis 72 s&auml;testatud ravikindlustusskeemi kohaseid h&uuml;vitisi, tingimusel et nad maksavad asjakohaseid makseid, mis on arvutatud l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud toetuse p&otilde;hjal, ega ole kindlustatud &uuml;hegi muu &otilde;igusaktil p&otilde;hineva ravikindlustusskeemi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> During the period for which he is entitled to received the allowance, the former member of the temporary staff shall continue to acquire further rights to retirement pension based on the salary attaching to his grade and step, provided that the contribution provided for in the Staff Regulations by reference to that salary is paid during that period and provided that the total pension does not exceed the maximum specified in Title II, Chapter 6 of the Conditions of Employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Ajavahemikul, mil tal on &otilde;igus saada toetust, kogub endine ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;taja oma palgaastmel ja -j&auml;rgul p&otilde;hinevat vanaduspensioni, tingimusel et ta maksab sel ajavahemikul personalieeskirjade kohaseid kindlustusmakseid, mis on arvutatud k&otilde;nealuse palga p&otilde;hjal, ja kogupension ei &uuml;leta teenistustingimuste II jaotise 6. peat&uuml;kis piiritletud &uuml;lemm&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of Article 5 of Annex VIII to the Staff Regulations, such period shall be considered to be a period of service. </inglise>
<eesti> Personalieeskirjade VIII lisa artikli 5 kohaldamisel k&auml;sitletakse sellist ajavahemikku teenistusajana. </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to Articles 1 (1) and 22 of Annex VIII to the Staff Regulations, the surviving spouse of a former member of the temporary staff who dies while in receipt of the monthly allowance provided for in paragraph 1 shall be entitled, provided that he or she has been his or her spouse for at least one year when the former member of the temporary staff left the service of the institution, to a survivor's pension equal to 60 % of the retirement pension which, irrespective of length of service or of age, would have been payable to the former member of the temporary staff if he or she had qualified for it at the time of death. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui personalieeskirjade VIII lisa artikli 1 l&otilde;ikest 1 v&otilde;i artiklist 22 ei tulene teisiti, on l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud igakuist toetust saava endise ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja surma korral tema lesel &otilde;igus, tingimusel et endise ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja institutsiooni teenistusest lahkumise hetkel oli ta tema abikaasaks olnud v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he aasta, saada toitjakaotuspensioni, mille suurus on 60% vanaduspensionist, mida oleks endisele ajutisele t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teenistuse kestusest v&otilde;i vanusest olenemata makstud, kui tal oleks olnud surmahetkel &otilde;igus seda saada. </eesti>
<inglise> The survivor's pension referred to in the first subparagraph shall not be less than the amounts specified in Title II, Chapter 6 of the Conditions of Employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud toitjakaotuspension ei ole v&auml;iksem kui teenistustingimuste II jaotise 6. peat&uuml;kis piiritletud summad. </eesti>
<inglise> However, in no case may it exceed the amount of the first payment of the retirement pension to which the former member of the temporary staff would have been entitled had he survived and been granted a retirement pension when he ceased to be eligible for the allowance referred to above. </inglise>
<eesti> Siiski ei v&otilde;i see mingil juhul &uuml;letada vanaduspensioni esimese v&auml;ljamakse summat, mille endine ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;taja oleks saanud, kui ta oleks elus ja talle oleks eespool osutatud toetuse saamise &otilde;iguse l&otilde;ppemisel m&auml;&auml;ratud vanaduspension. </eesti>
<inglise> The duration of the marriage stipulated in the first subparagraph shall not be taken into account if there are one or more children of a marriage contracted by the former member of the temporary staff before he left the service, provided that the surviving spouse maintains, or has maintained, those children. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud abielukestust ei arvestata, kui endisel ajutisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on enne teenistusest lahkumist s&otilde;lmitud abielust laps v&otilde;i lapsed ja kui lesk peab neid &uuml;lal v&otilde;i on neid &uuml;lal pidanud. </eesti>
<inglise> The same shall apply if the death of the former member of the temporary staff resulted from one of the circumstances referred to at the end of the second subparagraph of Article 17 of Annex VIII to the Staff Regulations. </inglise>
<eesti> Sama kehtib ka siis, kui endise ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja surma p&otilde;hjustas &uuml;ks personalieeskirjade VIII lisa artikli 17 teise l&otilde;igu l&otilde;pus nimetatud asjaoludest. </eesti>
<inglise> 9. </inglise>
<eesti> 9. </eesti>
<inglise> On the death of a former member of the temporary staff in receipt of the allowance provided for in paragraph 1, dependent children within the meaning of Article 2 of Annex VII to the Staff Regulations shall be entitled to an orphan's pension on the conditions set out in Title II, Chapter 6 of the Conditions of Employment and in Article 21 of Annex VIII to the Staff Regulations. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud toetust saava endise ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;taja surma korral on personalieeskirjade VII lisa artiklis 2 m&auml;&auml;ratletud &uuml;lalpeetavatel lastel &otilde;igus saada orvupensioni teenistustingimuste II jaotise 6. peat&uuml;kis ja personalieeskirjade VIII lisa artiklis 21 s&auml;testatud tingimustel. </eesti>
 